Exceptions and Other Licenses:

The spirit of this work and much of its content are taken from tomassedovic's[1] Rust roguelike tutorial[2], itself a port of the older Python roguelike tutorial[3], used as provided without any visible license.

The Square font by Wouter Van Oortmerssen[4] is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 Unported (CC BY 3.0) license[5]. The image "square10x10.png" is a derived work from Wouter's TTF font source[6] transformed into a png using ttf2png[7], with the second and third rows of text in the font copied from "arial10x10.png" by tomassedovic[1] under the Do What The F*ck You Want To public license (WTFPL) [8,9].

The project also makes use of libtcod[10] in binary form under its bespoke license[11, 12] of SDL in binary form[13] under the zlib license[14], and of the tcod-rs rust bindings for libtcod, by Tomas Sedovic[1] also used under the WTFPL[8,9].



